```

Wait — the "else" hint should use a real project name if we can detect one cheaply. But for `trace logs`, we don't know the projects unless we inspect the log entries. We can:
```typescript
// After fetching logs, extract unique project IDs from results for the hint
if (!projectFilter && logs.length > 0) {
  // TraceLog has "project.id" (numeric) — not ideal for hints
  // Just suggest the syntax:
  hint = `Filter by project: sentry trace logs ${org}/<project>/${traceId}`;
}
```

For `trace logs`, `TraceLog` only has `project.id` (numeric), not `project_slug`. So the multi-project hint can't list project names cheaply. That's fine — the generic syntax hint is still helpful. For `trace view` and `span list`, we have `project_slug` on spans so we can list real names.

